f=Brand Studio/rio/custom/ad-thresholds/SKILL.md · in=ad-thresholds rio's spend-guardrail engine: active campaign checked cadence against operator's configured rules daily caps, ROAS floors, kill criteria, scaling rules deterministic verdicts (HOLD KILL-recommend SCALE-recommend ESCALATE) recommendation carrying numbers. fiduciary-guard's fast-loop sibling: board gates *budget*; skill patrols burns, day day. · p=Paid ads fail through unattended arithmetic: campaign three days under ROAS floor bleeding quietly, winner starved because nobody scaled it, "small" daily raise compounding past what anyone approved. guardrails make triggered event instead month-end discovery whatever thresholds fit business $20/day local shop $2K/day venture run engine). · wu=Triggers: "scale ad," "kill threshold," "how campaigns doing against rules," configured check cadence (typically daily while campaigns run). · st:/ Protocol=`Load the rules (config: caps, floors, kill/scale criteria, escalation lines — never defaulted) \· -> Pull current campaign metrics (ad-platform connector or operator export; as-of dated) \· -> Check each campaign against each applicable rule \· -> Verdicts: WITHIN RULES / KILL-recommend (criteria met, numbers shown) \· / SCALE-recommend (criteria met; increment per config) / ESCALATE` · h3:Phase Load Rules=rio's config: `daily_cap`, `roas_floor` consecutive-days window triggers kill), `scale_rule` (what "winning" means increment), `spend_change_escalation_line`, `attribution_basis` (which ROAS counts click-through view-through, retargeting skill's honesty note). **Any unset rule check reports CONFIGURED, never made-up threshold** law fiduciary-guard. · h3:Phase 2 — Check=campaign: spend cap; ROAS (on configured attribution basis) floor, tracked across consecutive-days window; scale criteria; learning-phase protection (per ad-platform playbook don't thrash campaign platform still calibrating). · h3:Phase 3 — Verdicts=**KILL-recommend** floor breached configured window. Numbers shown; operator decides (config authorize auto-pause small spends explicit grant, never assumed)., **SCALE-recommend** win criteria met; increment config, never improvised. Repeated scaling crosses escalation line goes even mid-streak., **ESCALATE** any single-day spend change cumulative spend crossing configured lines routes operator, through board's fiduciary gate budget's approval scope exceeded (an campaign spend like any other). · h3:Phase Log Learn=verdict operator's call logs (append-only). Kill/scale outcomes feed kai's channel analysis; creative fatigue signals route pixel/pulse refresh; ROAS caveat rides report: **platform-reported ROAS platform grading homework** incrementality view-through inflation retargeting skill's gotchas, kai's independent numbers reconciliation point. · of=`## Guardrail Check: [date] — [brand] \·  \· \| Campaign \| Spend/day (cap) \| ROAS basis: [config] (floor) \| Days under \| Verdict \| \· \|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| \· ` · pr=**No configured rule, check never default.** Thresholds operator's risk appetite (fiduciary-guard's law, daily edition)., **Recommend; operator decides.** Auto-pause explicit config grant, small spends., **Scaling rules rules.** increment config; "it's crushing, double it" escalation, reflex., **Platform ROAS flagged self-graded.** Kai reconciles; incrementality caveats ride along., **Learning phases protected.** Thrashing calibrating campaigns known own-goal (playbook layer)., **Every verdict logs, ways.** Overrides included precedent's discipline. · f=connector operator exports cadence; checks run supplied numbers, as-of dated., Rules unset CONFIGURED check proposal session using catalog's shapes discussion starters (never silent defaults)., Metrics gap (platform outage, attribution break) verdicts suspend affected campaigns, stated; never guessed. · b:with Other Skills=**board's fiduciary-guard** gates budget envelope; skill patrols within it; crossing envelope goes back through board., `sales-retargeting` (sibling) owns strategy/segmentation; `ad-platform-mechanics` (sibling) owns volatile platform layer skill's learning-phase attribution notes cite., **pulse** hands proven-organic shortlist (the best creative candidates); **pixel** produces creative (spark-gated); **kai** owns independent measurement reconciliation; **nate** owns experiments new channel test nate's until it's standing campaign).